<taxonomicName id="DD2071AADDD6A9F2E5FE8EBDB5B35A5A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dario">B. dario</taxonomicName>
(synonyms: 
<taxonomicName id="152DD15EBA815023D1E7E9E0B32FE0A5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A99452E4-6948-4A70-85D0-9114F7B583D4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Cobitis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cobitis geto Hamilton 1822:355, 394" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geto">Cobitis geto</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="860A5D96FD56494CF9D2707FC4794278" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0A97801F-8B97-481C-B59C-4F8C97FCD0E9" authority="Chevrolat, 1837" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Diacantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Canthrophrys Diacantha flavicauda Swainson 1839:310" order="Coleoptera" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicauda">Diacantha flavicauda</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C31EB06F8C484FE134A569FA9E5627F2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1353834D-9E0B-4827-A7FE-29B67DF6F6F1" authority="Chevrolat, 1837" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Diacantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Canthrophrys Diacantha zebra Swainson 1839:310" order="Coleoptera" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zebra">D. zebra</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="A3C2636FBA0DA38C4DB496C1BBE6881C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE88716F-5BEC-4B82-8A00-79B7449E4FEA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia histrionica Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histrionica">B. histrionica</taxonomicName>
; b) the 
<taxonomicName id="9F78472ECF1926072595BBE1235635C2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:81AA95CE-4D06-49C7-8D6D-BAE996F30413" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia striata Narayan Rao 1920:60" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="striata">striata complex</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName id="F38E1D090E429631E4CC6D0FF6B58F0A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:81AA95CE-4D06-49C7-8D6D-BAE996F30413" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia striata Narayan Rao 1920:60" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="striata">B. striata</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3255BD56608026B8169BE4721E888D4" pageNumber="6">
Further, Menon merely mentions 
<taxonomicName id="2295C8943F7ACB391880C5DDB6CA8EDF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:912B4F20-D33E-4B47-8744-A126F6C5AFC0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia macrolineata Teugels, de Vos &amp; Snoeks 1986:188" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrolineata">B. macrolineata</taxonomicName>
in an addendum (p. 113) and 
<taxonomicName id="FF3FEC321BCACF29DC861822C86AF1AA" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E9426F35-7FF5-4AC7-837F-D7712F596F1B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia javedi Mirza &amp; Syed 1995:378" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="javedi">B. javedi</taxonomicName>
has been described since from Pakistan.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="94BCAF46F17A98F69998A57ED670DB24" pageNumber="7">
As for most Indian fish taxa presently recognised in the literature, it is doubtful whether Menon's species limits and synonymies will survive a critical revision based on fresh and well preserved material of various growth stages. Menon simply placed names in synonymy. He did not justify, discuss or explain any of his actions. It is not the place here to venture into a discussion of species-level systematics of Indian botiines; nevertheless, the geographic position of 
<taxonomicName id="C073A4D27A36A8F910A2A41E19A5031A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC02DE98-103C-4C0A-B517-3BFEC05198A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia kubotai Kottelat 2004:2" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kubotai">B. kubotai</taxonomicName>
at the extreme southeastern edge of the range of 
<taxonomicName id="4490CD0FE24B32D9AA656E14429F9C66" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:09226C1A-9A89-4F09-98CC-848F7DBB6275" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia Gray 1831:8" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Botia">Botia s.s.</taxonomicName>
and the existing material and information on botiine species recorded from the adjacent Salween and Irrawaddy drainages allows one to recognise this species as new and to suggest that it has no immediate relationships with any Indian species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B64D9368AC7E87E436B7D0F7B8F33E8" pageNumber="7">
Menon recorded a single species of 
<taxonomicName id="3C24394FCF39AB4B11D9EC82BE397A40" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:09226C1A-9A89-4F09-98CC-848F7DBB6275" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia Gray 1831:8" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Botia">Botia s.s.</taxonomicName>
from Myanmar, 
<taxonomicName id="420C7D06001A3C99E6262B63CF0A314D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE88716F-5BEC-4B82-8A00-79B7449E4FEA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia histrionica Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histrionica">B. histrionica</taxonomicName>
(see also Rendahl, 1948). Blyth's description of 
<taxonomicName id="26F0D08102D6467B47B3C65E6E53B671" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE88716F-5BEC-4B82-8A00-79B7449E4FEA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia histrionica Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histrionica">B. histrionica</taxonomicName>
is not very informative, but he described the colour pattern of the species here identified as 
<taxonomicName id="E21E9E40487855BC2E51739590AAE293" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE88716F-5BEC-4B82-8A00-79B7449E4FEA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia histrionica Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histrionica">B. histrionica</taxonomicName>
: &quot;The bands of the body are broad and subregular in shape, each containing a pale round spot at the lateral line and another on the ridge of the back&quot;. Day (1878) described and figured a single specimen, referring to Blyth's description and his 1870 paper in which he (Day) explicitly mentioned having examined a single specimen received from &quot;Major Berdmore at Pegu&quot;. This most likely is the 
<typeStatus id="7EEBFC6CC7E2A3789FD0EB4C34A5C0A3">holotype</typeStatus>
or a 
<typeStatus id="95A2C2D99AEBCA817546AE632E77263A">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="7CB99EF40BFE9E30599BC8E4AF6F38EE" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE88716F-5BEC-4B82-8A00-79B7449E4FEA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia histrionica Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histrionica">B. histrionica</taxonomicName>
. The drawing agrees with Blyth's description and the above diagnostic features.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2C68E06D094FA2398746459F82729D9F" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="C5708C781DD5169D094598E6B3C30CF5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC02DE98-103C-4C0A-B517-3BFEC05198A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia kubotai Kottelat 2004:2" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kubotai">Botia kubotai</taxonomicName>
is immediately distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="253478D283BB9B987CDD4D695E9C0C89" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE88716F-5BEC-4B82-8A00-79B7449E4FEA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia histrionica Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histrionica">B. histrionica</taxonomicName>
by its colour pattern (compare Figures 1 and 3). 
<taxonomicName id="7613C91298CF2434A39543C16A7BCF1A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE88716F-5BEC-4B82-8A00-79B7449E4FEA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia histrionica Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histrionica">Botia histrionica</taxonomicName>
has a yellowish brown body with 5 bars in positions identical to those of small 
<taxonomicName id="6DAD2BA1620624E69F0EA43F1356442A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC02DE98-103C-4C0A-B517-3BFEC05198A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia kubotai Kottelat 2004:2" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kubotai">B. kubotai</taxonomicName>
. The smallest individuals also have a few round pale spots in the bars and a vague indication of a midlateral stripe (vs. 3 stripes in 
<taxonomicName id="E6907AAE3CAAE27110BE314C2FF98C61" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC02DE98-103C-4C0A-B517-3BFEC05198A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia kubotai Kottelat 2004:2" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kubotai">B. kubotai</taxonomicName>
). But in larger individuals, the stripe disappears and the bars become very irregular or dissociated into blotches, resulting in a mainly pale coloured body with irregular dark markings, while in 
<taxonomicName id="763FCA2C6E277A08DE91234107868BB1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC02DE98-103C-4C0A-B517-3BFEC05198A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia kubotai Kottelat 2004:2" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kubotai">B. kubotai</taxonomicName>
colour pattern evolves from a relatively pale one towards a mostly black body with an 'organised' pattern of yellow spots and blotches. The black pattern on the fins of 
<taxonomicName id="E0A92BD083797BB79D67F6CCC7199247" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histronica">B. histronica</taxonomicName>
is also less extensive: the black band at dorsal-fin base is very narrow or absent (vs. broad), there is usually only one band on the pelvic (vs. two).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="89F8B216B147300EE283D6D4E88D5532" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="47D17B48A59DE217FCCC8AE51B6FAFDB" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE88716F-5BEC-4B82-8A00-79B7449E4FEA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia histrionica Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histrionica">Botia histrionica</taxonomicName>
was originally described from &quot;Tenasserim&quot; (Blyth, 1860: 166) but the type locality is listed as &quot;Pegu&quot; by Menon (1993: 43) and Menon &amp; Yazdani (1968: 120). Similar discrepancies between Blyth's published data and those appearing on later 
<collectionCode id="E577E0AB88CE2F61075FEDE0A481EEE3" collectionName="ZSI">ZSI</collectionCode>
labels are discussed by Ng &amp; Kottelat (2001) who concluded that there is no evidence to conclude that the label data are correct (they might be correct, but without supporting evidence it would be premature to accept them as correct). The &quot;Pegu&quot; localities possibly date back to Day (1870), but it seems clear from his various statements &quot;received from Berdmore at Pegu&quot;, &quot;received from Major Berdmore, Pegu&quot;, &quot;Pegu (Major Berdmore)&quot; that Pegu could have been the place of residence of Berdmore and not the place where he collected the fishes. For some species, Day unambiguously stated &quot;collected at Pegu&quot;, but we have no way to know whether this was a guess or based on actual data.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="32ECCD897C45C683D70613188107E73A" pageNumber="8">
Kottelat &amp; Chu (1987) reported botiines from the Chinese stretches of the Irrawaddy (Fig. 3d) and Salween which they tentatively identified as 
<taxonomicName id="5A158CE3C6CE592A03DE5A8C4C9067CE" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:984BE833-9E77-424F-B454-753B7D0303E6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia rostrata Günther 1868:367" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rostrata">B. rostrata</taxonomicName>
. The specimens are no longer accessible for direct comparison, but they seem to be large 
<taxonomicName id="77959460D93249C034E5A954188E3760" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE88716F-5BEC-4B82-8A00-79B7449E4FEA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia histrionica Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="histrionica">B. histrionica</taxonomicName>
with the bars dissociated one step further. 
<taxonomicName id="09F7BB1BCC1B50DE9D68BEF9824C9383" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:984BE833-9E77-424F-B454-753B7D0303E6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia rostrata Günther 1868:367" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rostrata">Botia rostrata</taxonomicName>
is considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="71388E60E5D8863F0232BE6EDC7B75DA" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:675C7B4C-7B57-48BA-A93E-6A68987F7FD4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia almorhae Gray 1831:8" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="almorhae">B. almorhae</taxonomicName>
by Menon (1993), a species reported from the Himalayan foothills, from Darjeeling to Rajasthan.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F15509CB5AE9114D772F549A09F6F723" pageNumber="8">
Using Menon's (1993) key, 
<taxonomicName id="BB44D66A973A4CEB0BEEC259D1ABCA09" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC02DE98-103C-4C0A-B517-3BFEC05198A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia kubotai Kottelat 2004:2" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kubotai">B. kubotai</taxonomicName>
keys out as 
<taxonomicName id="5D48D9E380F9B788E814B3053CA446AF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:675C7B4C-7B57-48BA-A93E-6A68987F7FD4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia almorhae Gray 1831:8" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="almorhae">B. almorhae</taxonomicName>
. Menon describes 
<taxonomicName id="3BB51EA66617487398A50887CF3DC010" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:675C7B4C-7B57-48BA-A93E-6A68987F7FD4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia almorhae Gray 1831:8" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="almorhae">B. almorhae</taxonomicName>
as having a sexually dimorphic colour pattern; but he does not provide evidence to demonstrate that these colour patterns effectively correspond to different sexes. These colour patterns were apparently recognised as different species by earlier authors, but this also is not discussed by Menon. In the absence of material, I tentatively follow Menon's conclusions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F3085E16856803708F3905E7AE711C12" lastPageNumber="9" pageNumber="8">
The colour pattern of adult males 
<taxonomicName id="C476B5BF646AE39C1413815F0257E766" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:675C7B4C-7B57-48BA-A93E-6A68987F7FD4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia almorhae Gray 1831:8" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="almorhae">B. almorhae</taxonomicName>
is reminiscent of that of large 
<taxonomicName id="6DCC508D62B176852C1E06FA26BD5E30" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC02DE98-103C-4C0A-B517-3BFEC05198A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia kubotai Kottelat 2004:2" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kubotai">B. kubotai</taxonomicName>
with its pale spots surrounded by a blackish background (the rendering of the published illustrations does not allow to recognize if there is an organised pattern in the distribution of the spots). There are more bands on the caudal fin (7, vs. 3-4 in 
<taxonomicName id="0DC40D0B3BF0C09533C714AB7AE62265" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC02DE98-103C-4C0A-B517-3BFEC05198A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia kubotai Kottelat 2004:2" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kubotai">B. kubotai</taxonomicName>
), on the pectoral fin (5, vs. 2-3) and on the dorsal fin (3, vs. 2). The pattern of the females and juveniles 
<taxonomicName id="F5AF699C69B043B62FC6D8F5E17298FD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:675C7B4C-7B57-48BA-A93E-6A68987F7FD4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia almorhae Gray 1831:8" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="almorhae">B. almorhae</taxonomicName>
is conspicuously distinct. It is missing the three stripes of 
<taxonomicName id="898F3FC595A4414414C21D0A416226DD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC02DE98-103C-4C0A-B517-3BFEC05198A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia kubotai Kottelat 2004:2" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kubotai">B. kubotai</taxonomicName>
and the second, third and fourth bars are Y-shaped, leaving a pale triangular saddle along dorsal mid-line; between each pair of bars, on the lateral line, there is a vertically elongated blotch. Problems of identification of 
<taxonomicName id="8F8E17708DA3903786DC437D9947C68C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:675C7B4C-7B57-48BA-A93E-6A68987F7FD4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia almorhae Gray 1831:8" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="almorhae">B. almorhae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8FDB1B3A6A47A09DD21D8466758FAFA8" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:58B6D657-3D57-48FA-9133-0C853EBA8BEB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia birdi Chaudhuri 1909:339" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="birdi">B. birdi</taxonomicName>
are discussed by Kullander et al. (1999).
